@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-4">
    <h1 class="mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    
    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
            <p class="text-muted"><em>Last Updated: November 8, 2025</em></p>
            
            <p class="lead">
                KF Construction is committed to protecting your privacy and maintaining the security of your personal information. 
                This Privacy Policy outlines our practices concerning the collection, use, and disclosure of your information in 
                accordance with North Dakota state laws and applicable federal regulations.
            </p>

            <h3 class="mt-4">1. Information We Collect</h3>
            <p>We collect several types of information to provide and improve our services:</p>
            
            <h5 class="mt-3">Personal Information You Provide:</h5>
            <ul>
                <li>Name, email address, phone number, and mailing address</li>
                <li>Account credentials (username and password)</li>
                <li>Payment and billing information for services rendered</li>
                <li>Project details and service requests</li>
                <li>Communications and correspondence with our company</li>
            </ul>

            <h5 class="mt-3">Automatically Collected Information:</h5>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>IP Address:</strong> We collect and store your Internet Protocol (IP) address for security, fraud prevention, and system administration purposes. IP addresses are securely stored and are only accessible to authorized system administrators with proper credentials.</li>
                <li>Browser type, operating system, and device information</li>
                <li>Pages visited, time spent on pages, and navigation patterns</li>
                <li>Access times and referring website addresses</li>
                <li>Session cookies for authentication and functionality</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="mt-4">2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
            <p>Your information is used for legitimate business purposes, including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Providing construction and related services</li>
                <li>Processing payments and maintaining accurate financial records</li>
                <li>Communicating about projects, appointments, and service updates</li>
                <li>Responding to inquiries and providing customer support</li>
                <li>Improving our website functionality and user experience</li>
                <li>Detecting and preventing unauthorized access, fraud, and security breaches</li>
                <li>Complying with North Dakota business record-keeping requirements</li>
                <li>Meeting legal and regulatory obligations</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="mt-4">3. IP Address Security and Access</h3>
            <p>We take the security of your IP address and other technical information seriously:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>IP addresses are encrypted in transit and at rest</li>
                <li>Access to IP address data is restricted to authorized administrators only</li>
                <li>All access to IP information is logged and monitored</li>
                <li>IP data is used solely for security monitoring, fraud prevention, and troubleshooting</li>
                <li>We do not sell, rent, or share IP addresses with third parties for marketing purposes</li>
                <li>IP addresses are retained only as long as necessary for security and legal compliance</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="mt-4">4. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h3>
            <p>We respect your privacy and limit disclosure of your personal information. We may share information only in these circumstances:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>With Your Consent:</strong> We will share information when you explicitly authorize us to do so</li>
                <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Third-party vendors who assist with payment processing, hosting, or business operations under strict confidentiality agreements</li>
                <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by North Dakota state law, federal law, court order, or other legal process</li>
                <li><strong>Protection of Rights:</strong> To protect our legal rights, property, safety, or the rights and safety of others</li>
                <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, with prior notice to affected parties</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We do not sell your personal information to third parties for their marketing purposes.</p>

            <h3 class="mt-4">5. Data Security Measures</h3>
            <p>We implement comprehensive security measures to protect your information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Industry-standard encryption (AES-256-GCM) for sensitive data at rest</li>
                <li>SSL/TLS encryption for all data transmitted over the internet</li>
                <li>Multi-factor authentication for administrative access</li>
                <li>Regular security audits and vulnerability assessments</li>
                <li>Role-based access controls limiting data access to authorized personnel only</li>
                <li>Secure backup systems with encryption</li>
                <li>Employee training on data privacy and security best practices</li>
                <li>Incident response procedures for potential data breaches</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="mt-4">6. Data Retention</h3>
            <p>We retain your personal information in accordance with North Dakota business record requirements and industry standards:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Active account information is retained for the duration of your business relationship with us</li>
                <li>Financial and tax records are retained for a minimum of seven (7) years as required by North Dakota law</li>
                <li>Project records are maintained for warranty and liability purposes</li>
                <li>Security logs, including IP addresses, are retained for up to one (1) year unless needed for ongoing investigations</li>
                <li>Upon account closure, personal information is securely deleted or anonymized within 90 days, except where retention is legally required</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="mt-4">7. Your Privacy Rights</h3>
            <p>As a North Dakota resident and customer, you have the following rights:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Right to Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal information we maintain about you</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your personal information, subject to legal retention requirements</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Portability:</strong> Receive your information in a structured, commonly used format</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Restrict Processing:</strong> Request limitation on how we use your information</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Object:</strong> Object to certain processing activities</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Non-Discrimination:</strong> We will not discriminate against you for exercising your privacy rights</li>
            </ul>
            <p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information provided below.</p>

            <h3 class="mt-4">8. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h3>
            <p>We use cookies and similar technologies for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for website functionality, authentication, and security</li>
                <li><strong>Performance Cookies:</strong> Help us understand how visitors use our website</li>
                <li><strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> Remember your preferences and settings</li>
            </ul>
            <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Note that disabling certain cookies may limit website functionality.</p>

            <h3 class="mt-4">9. Third-Party Links</h3>
            <p>Our website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before providing any personal information.</p>

            <h3 class="mt-4">10. Children's Privacy</h3>
            <p>Our services are intended for adults and businesses. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 years of age. If we become aware that we have collected information from a child under 13, we will take immediate steps to delete such information.</p>

            <h3 class="mt-4">11. Data Breach Notification</h3>
            <p>In the event of a data breach that compromises your personal information, we will:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Notify affected individuals without unreasonable delay</li>
                <li>Report the breach to appropriate North Dakota authorities as required by law</li>
                <li>Provide information about the nature of the breach and steps being taken</li>
                <li>Offer guidance on protective measures you can take</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="mt-4">12. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h3>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices, technology, legal requirements, or other factors. We will:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Post the updated policy on this page with a new "Last Updated" date</li>
                <li>Notify users of material changes via email or prominent website notice</li>
                <li>Maintain prior versions for your reference upon request</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Your continued use of our services after changes become effective constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

            <h3 class="mt-4">13. North Dakota-Specific Provisions</h3>
            <p>This Privacy Policy complies with North Dakota Century Code requirements regarding:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Business record retention and confidentiality</li>
                <li>Consumer protection standards</li>
                <li>Data security breach notification requirements</li>
                <li>Fair business practices</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="mt-4">14. Contact Information</h3>
            <p>If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us:</p>
            <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
                <strong>KF Construction</strong><br>
                Email: Use the contact form on our website<br>
                Response Time: We will respond to privacy-related inquiries within 30 days<br>
                <br>
                <em>For security reasons, we require identity verification for requests involving access to or deletion of personal information.</em>
            </div>

            <h3 class="mt-4">15. Consent</h3>
            <p>By using our website and services, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described herein. If you do not agree with this policy, please discontinue use of our services.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
